Hi,

I tried the following toy Verilog code:

@
module gatebit (
	input inbit,
	output wire outbit
);

assign outbit = ~inbit;

endmodule


module testbit (
	input inbit,
	output wire outbit
);

wire [2:0] path;
//wire path [2:0];

gatebit u0(.inbit(inbit), .outbit(path[0]));
gatebit u1(.inbit(path[0]), .outbit(path[1]));
gatebit u2(.inbit(path[1]), .outbit(path[2]));
gatebit u3(.inbit(path[2]), .outbit(outbit));

endmodule
@

and Verilator reported a false warning ("Signal unoptimizable: Feedback to clock or circular logic"). Apparently, Verilator checks for feedback at only variable name level. Isn't it too hard to let it check down to single-wire level?

Kind regards,

Cong-Van
